  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.ManagementWorkspaceSubtitleTenant">Manage stores, assign staff, maintain the tenant catalog, and direct how each store sees the catalog.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.ManagementWorkspaceSubtitleStore">Manage assigned clerks, keep store stock ready, and maintain the products assigned to the selected store.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.ManagementWorkspaceSubtitleAssigned">This area is reserved for assigned management tasks.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.CreateUserHelpTenant">Tenant admins can create store managers and clerks for the current tenant.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.CreateUserHelpStore">Store managers can create clerks for their assigned stores.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.CatalogHelpTenant">Create tenant base products and review how stores use them.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.CatalogHelpStore">Browse the products assigned to the selected store and manage their sellable store variants separately.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.TeamTabDescriptionTenant">Manage the people in this tenant. Open a team member to review store access and assign or remove stores.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.TeamTabDescriptionStore">Manage the clerks in your store scope and control which stores they can access.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.StoresTabDescriptionTenant">Review every store in this tenant and create new ones when the business expands.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.StoresTabDescriptionStore">Review the stores available in your current scope.</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="Loc.CatalogTabDescriptionTenant">Maintain tenant-level base products from here.</sys:String>
